
üå± Welcome

This guide gives you one simple path to install, run, and explore the Smart-Plant-Guardian system.
Total setup time: 5 minutes.

For detailed documentation, see:

README.md

docs/project_overview.md



---

1Ô∏è‚É£ Requirements

Hardware (for live data)

Arduino Nicla Sense ME

Arduino MKR WiFi 1010

USB cables

WiFi or Personal Hotspot (or Cedalo MQTT broker)


Software

Python 3.10+

Git

Pip or Conda



---

2Ô∏è‚É£ Clone the Repository

git clone https://github.com/<your-username>/Smart-Plant-Guardian.git
cd Smart-Plant-Guardian


---

3Ô∏è‚É£ Create Python Environment

python3 -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate      # macOS/Linux
.venv\Scripts\activate         # Windows

pip install -r requirements.txt


---

4Ô∏è‚É£ Create Your .env File

Create a file at the project root named .env with:

MQTT_BROKER=pf-eveoxy0ua6xhtbdyohag.cedalo.cloud
MQTT_PORT=1883
MQTT_TOPIC=smartplant/real/#

SERIAL_PORT=/dev/tty.usbmodemXXXX
SERIAL_BAUD=115200

SQLITE_DB=data/database/plant_data.sqlite

EMAIL_USER=smartplantlabs@outlook.com
EMAIL_PASS=YOUR_APP_PASSWORD


---

5Ô∏è‚É£ Initialise the SQLite Database

Run this once:

python - <<'EOF'
from src.utils.db_helpers import create_tables
create_tables()
print("Database initialised ‚úî")
EOF

This creates:

data/database/plant_data.sqlite

data/raw/ folder (empty)



---

6Ô∏è‚É£ Choose How Data Will Be Collected


---

Option A ‚Äî MQTT Mode (MKR WiFi 1010)

1. Upload src/acquisition/arduino/mkr_wifi_plant_mqtt.ino


2. Start the MQTT subscriber:



python src/acquisition/mqtt_subscriber.py

You should now see new data arriving in the DB.


---

Option B ‚Äî Serial Mode (Nicla Sense ME)


1. Upload nicla_sense_plant_sensor.ino


2. Run:



python src/acquisition/serial_subscriber.py


---

7Ô∏è‚É£ Launch the Dashboard

Open a second terminal:

python src/dashboard/dashboard.py

Then open:
http://127.0.0.1:8050

You will see:

Temperature graph

Humidity graph

VOC graph

Pressure graph

Plant health score

Plant photo

Email alert tab



---

8Ô∏è‚É£ Where Your Data Goes

Raw CSV


data/raw/readings_YYYY-MM-DD.csv

SQLite Database

data/database/plant_data.sqlite
Contains timestamps, sensor values & metadata.

Metadata

metadata/*.json
Experiment info, calibration details, peace lily profile.


---

9Ô∏è‚É£ Analysis (Optional)

jupyter notebook src/analysis/exploratory_analysis.ipynb


---

üîü Running Tests

pytest -q


---

1Ô∏è‚É£1Ô∏è‚É£ Troubleshooting

Dashboard shows ‚ÄúNo Data‚Äù

Is MQTT subscriber running?

Or Serial subscriber?

Check the database size with:


sqlite3 data/database/plant_data.sqlite "SELECT COUNT(*) FROM readings;"

Serial Port Busy

Close Arduino IDE Serial Monitor. Only one app can access the port.

MQTT not connecting

Try:

mosquitto_sub -h pf-eveoxy0ua6xhtbdyohag.cedalo.cloud -t "#" -v


---

1Ô∏è‚É£2Ô∏è‚É£ Quick Demo (No Hardware Needed)

1. Drop any CSV into data/raw/


2. Run:



python src/utils/csv_to_sqlite.py
python src/dashboard/dashboard.py

Dashboard loads historical data.


